entry %archaic <seen> %archaic <body> !+ <see> (test.) test
affix .adj-1 @nominalizers <seen>%archaic adjectival 1
entry <new bright> <sun>%archaic.adj-1 (adj.) new bright


entry <water> *ŋuʃi (na.) water
entry <water>.pl *ʔuʃi +! *ŋuʃi (unknown.) ??
entry <earth> *puriqa (ni.) earth
entry <earth>.pl *ʔuri +! *puriqa (unknown.) ??


entry <wet> <wet>%archaic (adj.) wet, damp
entry <sweat> %archaic <wet>.c8 (ni.) sweat, perspiration
entry <hippo> %archaic <wet>.c3 (na.) hippopotamus, large river dwelling mammal
 
entry <rock> %archaic <rock>.c8 (ni.) rock, boulder
entry <turnip> %archaic <rock>.c7 (na.) turnip
entry <armadillo> %archaic <rock>.c5 (ni.) armadillo
entry <pebble> <rock>%archaic.dim (na.) pebble
entry <rockslide> %archaic <rock>.pl (ni.) rockslide, avalanche
entry <hard> <rock>%archaic (adj.) hard, stern, solid, stable

entry <pack> %archaic <beast>.pl (ni.) pack, group of animals

entry <big> <fear>%archaic (adj.) great, big

entry <mountain range> %archaic <mountain>.pl (ni.) mountain range

affix .aug @ancient-derivations %archaic afxs.<big>.afxe augmentative (always inanimate)
affix .dim @ancient-derivations %archaic afxs.<child>.afxe diminutive (always animate)

entry <give> *kasu (vd.) to give

entry <village> <people>%archaic.gen (ni.) village, settlement

entry <warrior> %archaic <sword>.c1 (nh.) warrior, soldier
entry <slice> %archaic <sword>.vbz (vt.) to slice, to cut



